4 HJR___ URGING THE STATE COMMITTEE OF PUBLIC HEALTH TO REVIEW
5 AND CONSIDER ADDING THE NOVEL SYNTHETIC OPIOID
6 N-PROPIONITRILE CHLORPHINE AS A SCHEDULE I CONTROLLED
7 SUBSTANCE.
8
9 WHEREAS, the synthetic opioid known as Cychlorphine
10 (N-Propionitrile Chlorphine) has emerged as a lethal threat
11 in the illicit drug market, with in vitro pharmacological
12 data indicating it is approximately 10 times more potent
13 than fentanyl; and
14 WHEREAS, because of its extreme potency, even small
15 doses of Cychlorphine can cause rapid respiratory depression
16 and failure, leading to a significantly higher risk of
17 accidental overdose and death compared to existing
18 controlled substances; and
19 WHEREAS, Cychlorphine has been identified by forensic
20 laboratories in multiple states and has been linked to a
21 rising number of fatalities, often appearing in counterfeit
22 pills and/or in combination with other substances without
23 the user's knowledge; and
24 WHEREAS, this substance possesses a high potential
25 for abuse and has no currently accepted medical use in the
26 United States; now therefore,
27 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
28 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That we hereby formally request
Page 1

HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That we hereby formally request
HJR281 INTRODUCED
29 and direct the State Committee of Public Health to
30 immediately exercise its administrative authority to review
31 and consider adding N-Propionitrile Chlorphine
32 (Cychlorphine) to the list of Schedule I controlled
33 substances based on the set of factors included in Section
34 20-2-20 of the Code of Alabama 1975.
35 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, That a copy of this
36 resolution be transmitted to the State Health Officer of the
37 Alabama Department of Public Health and the members of the
38 State Committee of Public Health to ensure the swift
39 implementation of this process.
